The article is a statement by the Press Secretary regarding the House vote on the GOP Payroll Tax Cut Plan. The statement emphasizes the need for Congress to prevent a tax hike that would affect 160 million Americans and calls on Republicans to stop playing politics and prioritize the middle class. The Press Secretary highlights the importance of extending a tax cut worth $1,000 for the average family and urges Congress to pass it before going on vacation. The statement expresses the expectation that Republicans and Democrats will come to an agreement in the eleventh hour to protect the middle class and complete their budget work for the year.